{%- comment -%}
SNIPPET:
  icons.Liquid

USAGE:
  {%- include "icons", icon: "search" -%}

PARAMETERS:
  {string} icon[ = "all" ] // The icon to render.
  {string} class[ = "_icon" ] // The class to use.  Defaults to "_icon".

OUTPUT:
  - An <svg> for the selected icon.
  - If no "icon" parameter is provided, all icons are rendered.
  - If an invalid "icon" parameter is provided, an "unknown" icon is rendered.
  - If no "class" parameter is provided, it defaults to "_icon".

DESCRIPTION:
  - This file contains all icons for the Boni theme as <svg> snippets.
  - All <svg>s are arranged in a switch/case statement.
  - If no icon identifier is provided, they are all rendered.
  - A default "unknown" icon is provided, as fallthrough.
  - This implementation has desireable benefits.  It allows us to:
      - Manage all icons together.
      - Conveniently render all icons quickly and easily, for debugging.
      - Avoid issues with {% include "icon-menu" %} wrapping the file with
        additional classes behind the scenes.
      - Provide global wrappers we want for all icons, such as class names.

RESOURCES:
  https://stackoverflow.com/questions/28507597/using-svg-icons-in-shopify
  https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/SVG/Tutorial/Fills_and_Strokes
  https://www.w3.org/TR/SVG/coords.html
  https://www.w3.org/Graphics/SVG/IG/resources/svgprimer.html

